keyValuePair.Value: Were you outclassed by a better team over the two legs?

I'm not sure if you thought your team could come back in the tie but it looked as if the players didn't really believe it was possible. Are you worried what those two defeats will do to your boys' confidence?
We'll have to learn from this experience.

%1s are a very good team and they were better than us. I don't think we ever really got a foothold in either of the two games, in spite of all our hard work. Those two defeats are tough to take but I'm sure we'll learn from this experience. Technically and tactically we have to improve.
We've been knocked out by a very good team.
Of course I'm disappointed. I expected more from our boys and we were desperate to go through. But sometimes you just have to hold your hands up. We've been beaten by a very good team.
We've got so much to learn.

Fair play. They're a very good team. But we made it easy for them, didn't we? I wonder about some of the decision-making out there. Individually and collectively, we just have to better defensively if we're going to take the club forward.
Beaten twice, was this a lesson for your boys?
That's two defeats at the hands of %1s and you've missed out on a place in the semi-final. It's a bitter pill but would you admit you'd probably gone as far as you could in the competition?
%1s could go on and win it.

It was a tough draw for us, getting %1s at this stage of the competition. They look to me like a team that could go on and lift the trophy. As hard as we tried to crowd them and deny them space, they were always a step ahead of us in both games. We can take lessons from how they play.
%1s could go on and lift the trophy now.
We really thought we could give %1s a game when the draw was made. But credit to them. They've been better than us in both games. I think we may have been knocked out by the eventual winners.
I wanted more from us, to be honest.

Of course they're a good team. But we never looked as if we thought we could beat them. We got caught in the transitions in both games. They always seemed ahead of us. If you can't put pressure on the opposition, you just going to hand them the initiative.
You're out after two defeats. What went wrong?
You must have thought, up against %1s, you had a chance of qualifying. But they've beaten you twice and you're out. Why didn't it happen for your boys over these two games?
We have to bounce back now.

We expected to progress in the competition but we've been caught out twice by clever opponents. We have to recover quickly from this. It'll be no good going into our next game feeling sorry for ourselves. It's time to show some character.

We expected to progress in the competition but we've been caught out twice by clever opponents. We have to recover quickly from this. It'll be no good going into our next game feeling sorry for ourselves. It's time to show some character.
%1s took full advantage in both games.
%1s are a good team but I'm not sure they're that much better than us. We have to congratulate them on going through, though. And look at ourselves to identify where we need to improve.
We were careless on the ball in both games.
We were careless on the ball in both games.

We have standards at %1s so I'm disappointed. I'm not sure there was that much between the teams, but we were too careless on the ball in both games. They were never really in trouble, were they? They're the ones qualifying. We're the ones who've thrown it away.

We have standards at %1s so I'm disappointed. I'm not sure there was that much between the teams, but we were too careless on the ball in both games. They were never really in trouble, were they? They're the ones qualifying. We're the ones who've thrown it away.
On the brink of the Final, why couldn't your boys find a performance?
Maybe you believed you could come back from that first leg defeat against %1s. But you didn't seem to make any difference. Did your boys just buckle under pressure in both games?
I take my share of the blame.
I take my share of the blame.

Sometimes you can worry too much about the opposition. Maybe I put too much pressure on the boys expecting them to hold out. Right now, I regret not having set up a more adventurous team. We couldn't have done any worse, that's for sure.

Sometimes you can worry too much about the opposition. Maybe I put too much pressure on the boys expecting them to hold out. Right now, I regret not having set up a more adventurous team. We couldn't have done any worse, that's for sure.
We did well to get this far, I think.
We're a developing team. We make mistakes. I make mistakes, too. But we'll learn and be better. I'm actually proud the boys managed to get this far in the competition. We'll be back!
We were a mess, to be honest.

Maybe it was the pressure of a semi-final. We had a game plan but we messed up in both games. Too many of our lads lost their discipline and went chasing the ball instead of keeping our shape. And we paid the price. Twice.
Was this always too big a challenge for your boys?
%1s got the draw today that has taken them through. After being so badly beaten in the first leg, did you ever believe your team could get back into the tie?
It was about pride today.

It's fair to say the first leg decided the tie. We were playing for pride here and I think we restored a bit of that. Good spirit, good work-rate. But I don't think we ever had enough quality up front to go through.
It's a blow but we'll recover from it.
We knew it would be tough in both games and losing the first leg gave us too much to do here. The boys just have to get over it now and come back ready for the games we've got coming up.
We can't get away with performances like that.

I think it's obvious why we're out of the competition. Against clever opponents, you have to better-organised and more resilient than we were in the first leg. You can't play like that and expect to get away with it. We huffed and puffed today but we never looked like we were going to get back into the tie.
That's the dream over. How will your boys respond?

On the brink of the Final, I'm sure you expected some fight from your team. The defeat in the first leg made it difficult, of course, but are you disappointed your boys could do no more than draw today?
We lacked self-belief.

I can give a big speech in the dressing room beforehand, but it's about the players believing in themselves, isn't it? At least we made a better fist of it today in terms of effort and commitment, but our confidence was shot after that first leg hammering.
We need to mature as a team.

It's been a great run to get this far. We've learnt a lot along the way. And we've learnt a lot from these two games, too. We need to be more decisive in the key moments. But this team will improve, that's for sure.
I don't think we were brave enough.

Look, we took a big beating in the first leg and you could see, psychologically, we'd been damaged by that. We didn't ever look brave enough today to turn things round. We needed to take more risks to have any chance of getting through to the %1s Final.
Were the team just not good enough?
Were the team just not good enough?

It's a shame to see %1s slip out of the %2s with the semi-finals in sight. Defeat in the first leg cost your boys, didn't it? Were you surprised they didn't give a better account of themselves today, though?

It's a shame to see %1s slip out of the %2s with the semi-finals in sight. Defeat in the first leg cost your boys, didn't it? Were you surprised they didn't give a better account of themselves today, though?
There's work to do, that's for sure.

Look, we ran and ran but sometimes that's not enough. We didn't look sure of ourselves at either end of the pitch. We need better technique and a bit more composure. We tried to get back into it today, but I think we know we've got work to do as a team.
We'd hoped to give our fans a comeback to remember.

Our supporters have been right behind us all the way to the quarter finals. We probably had too much to do today to recover from that first leg defeat, but I'm still sorry we didn't put on a better show for those fans.

Our supporters have been right behind us all the way to the quarter finals. We probably had too much to do today to recover from that first leg defeat, but I'm still sorry we didn't put on a better show for those fans.
I expected more from the boys.
I expected more from the boys.

To be successful, you need to have self-belief. I'm not sure we've got enough of that in the %1s dressing room. Too many of our lads looked like they were just trying not to make mistakes, instead of imposing themselves on the game. We never looked like getting back into the tie today, did we?
That first leg defeat has cost you, hasn't it?
You showed some spirit today, but you needed better than this draw to give you a chance of making progress in the %1s. How bitterly do you regret that first leg defeat now?
We were always going to struggle today.

That first leg defeat put us under a lot of pressure. I'm not sure what more the boys could have done today. It was tough. We didn't want to get overrun again, but that meant we weren't ready to commit men in attack to put the opposition under pressure.
We didn't do enough, to be honest.

If we'd started strong and put %1s straight under pressure, who knows what might have happened? But they're an experienced team. They slowed the game down and stopped us playing. They knew a draw was enough for them.
We were too far behind.

Our awful defensive performance in the first game meant we were always going to have too much to do here. We conceded those terrible goals in the first leg and that's why we're out of the competition.
What more could your boys have done?

The first leg defeat looked to have put the tie beyond you. But your team came back strongly today. Are you pleased with the display? Or just even more frustrated about what happened in the last game?
We restored a little pride.

We'd left ourselves with a big deficit to make up but, credit to the boys, they really took the challenge on and tried to make things happen against a very good team. We knew we were better than we showed in the first leg. At least we have a bit of pride back after today.
These are good, honest players.
These players have professional pride and wanted to make up for the terrible display in the first leg. And we actually came close to something special here. It just wasn't to be.
These players have professional pride and wanted to make up for the terrible display in the first leg. And we actually came close to something special here. It just wasn't to be.
It was all about the first leg.
It was all about the first leg.
When you look at how good we were today, it's frustrating. We were excellent. That display should have been taking us through, but our terrible performance in the first leg gave us too much to do.
When you look at how good we were today, it's frustrating. We were excellent. That display should have been taking us through, but our terrible performance in the first leg gave us too much to do.
It must hurt to miss out on the Final?
It must hurt to miss out on the Final?
Your team definitely did everything they could to make up for your poor display in the first leg of this semi. You must have been proud of their efforts. Are you frustrated to miss out on the Final?
Your team definitely did everything they could to make up for your poor display in the first leg of this semi. You must have been proud of their efforts. Are you frustrated to miss out on the Final?
It's about having self-respect.

Everybody - me, the team, the fans - knew we needed goals today to pull off an incredible comeback. We were close but we didn't make it. I just hope the supporters are proud of what they saw from the team. Let's take some inspiration and self-respect from this display.

Everybody - me, the team, the fans - knew we needed goals today to pull off an incredible comeback. We were close but we didn't make it. I just hope the supporters are proud of what they saw from the team. Let's take some inspiration and self-respect from this display.
The lads needed to prove a point today.

First of all, I've got to say I'm proud that this %1s team got this far in the %2s. And I'm proud of the effort we put in today, too. Our poor display in the first leg cost us big-time, but we've got a little self-respect as a team back now, at least.

First of all, I've got to say I'm proud that this %1s team got this far in the %2s. And I'm proud of the effort we put in today, too. Our poor display in the first leg cost us big-time, but we've got a little self-respect as a team back now, at least.
We should have been braver.

I think we had the opposition rocking today. If we'd been braver, shown a little more ambition, maybe we'd be here celebrating an incredible comeback. As it is, we've missed out on the Final. And I'm frustrated. I hate having regrets about what might have been.

I think we had the opposition rocking today. If we'd been braver, shown a little more ambition, maybe we'd be here celebrating an incredible comeback. As it is, we've missed out on the Final. And I'm frustrated. I hate having regrets about what might have been.
Was the tie already beyond you?

You'll be pleased with the win over %1s and your team's performance, of course. But you had so much to do after that disastrous first leg. Did you think you were ever in with a chance of reaching the semis?
It was too little too late.

I have to say the lads put in decent performances today. They took control of the game, definitely. But it was a bit late for that, wasn't it? A good win, of course. But we'd already surrendered the tie in the first leg, hadn't we?
That's a conversation for another time.
Of course we'll go back and analyse where we went wrong. Right now, though, the boys are shattered after the effort they put into this second leg and I need to pick them up in time for our next game.
It felt like we were already out.

We needed to make a strong, early impact on the game today. At first, though, we looked like we'd already surrendered. If the lads had been at it right from kick-off, maybe we could have pulled off a shock. As it is, that's us out of the %1s for this season.
Does that do anything to make up for the first leg defeat.
You're out, of course. But you must have been impressed with the team's spirit. For a while it looked as if you might even pull off a comeback. Are you pleased your boys restored some pride?
It's about results. Ours have to improve.

Of course we were better today. We couldn't have been any worse! I'm pleased the boys responded with a decent display but it was all too little, too late. Just look at the scoreline: we're out, aren't we? Results have to improve.

Of course we were better today. We couldn't have been any worse! I'm pleased the boys responded with a decent display but it was all too little, too late. Just look at the scoreline: we're out, aren't we? Results have to improve.
Maybe we should have set up differently in the first leg.
Maybe we should have set up differently in the first leg.
Of course the boys had a go here. I wouldn't have expected anything less from them. We made all our own problems in the first leg, though. In hindsight, we weren't set up right at all for that game.
I think despite the difference we could have progressed in the %1s. I blame myself for not starting the game in a more offensive formation.
We can't play like we did in the first leg and expect to go through.

Yes, we were better here. We restored a little pride in the shirt. But we were never going to get back in the tie, to be honest. The performance in the first leg gave us too much to ever recover from. And we never looked capable of turning it round.
A fantastic comeback. Did you expect that from your team?
After your heavy defeat in the first leg, nobody could have predicted what happened today. You tore into the opposition and they went to pieces. How proud are you of what the boys have achieved?
We looked a hungry team today.

The boys were well aware they'd let everyone down in the first leg. But they've been determined all week to go out and prove people wrong. And the whole team responded today. I'm very happy we've qualified. Now we've got to find some consistency.
Qualification was always our objective.

Getting through was an important target for us. We did it the hard way but well done to the boys for the comeback. We're where we want to be. Now we have to make we don't repeat our mistakes from the first leg ever again!
We made a statement today.

We were in a very awkward situation after the first leg. The lads knew they were nowhere near good enough. But they made up for that here, didn't they? I'm proud we kept going. We deserved to qualify after pulling off this comeback. I think we've made a real statement today.
What a comeback from %1s to reach the Final. You must be ecstatic?
What a comeback from %1s to reach the Final. You must be ecstatic?

After that heavy defeat in the first leg, it looked like you'd missed your chance. But today's performance and an incredible comeback defied everybody's expectations. How proud will you be to lead %1s out at the Final?

After that heavy defeat in the first leg, it looked like you'd missed your chance. But today's performance and an incredible comeback defied everybody's expectations. How proud will you be to lead %1s out at the Final?
We'll need more of that now.

People said a %1s comeback would be impossible. Well, I'm glad nobody told my players. They were sensational today. They chased and harried and they took their chances. We need to see more of that. If they play like they did today, we'll have a really good chance in the Final.
Let's focus on the Final now.
The boys were unbelievable today. I couldn't be happier. But we need to keep our feet on the ground. There's no point getting to the Final if we don't go there in the right frame of mind to win it.
That performance has been coming!

I've been very encouraged how this %1s team's been developing and it was a great day today. The players were intent on making up for their first leg mistakes. That determination is what made the comeback possible. I'm proud of them all.
What made that comeback possible?
It was a great comeback and a remarkable achievement. How did you pull it off? What made the difference today?
That attitude can take us all the way.

The boys have worked so hard in training this week and I thought the more experienced players led the charge here. We had nothing to lose after the first leg and maybe that gave us the courage we needed. With that attitude, perhaps now we can go all the way.
We'll try to keep calm now.

It was an amazing way to get through to a semi-final. But, as well as celebrating, we need to look at what we need to do to better. I hope we won't need another comeback like that to help us reach the Final!
We played without any fear.

The pressure got to us in the first leg, but we played without fear today. Our attacking play was far too much for the opposition to handle and we got goals at just the right times. I'm very proud of what we've achieved here.
A brilliant comeback. Are you happy? Or relieved?
It didn't look as though you'd be able to make it through to the next round after that terrible defeat in the first leg. But what a comeback! How did your boys turn things round?
A performance to be proud of, eh?

I think the lads showed the opposition too much respect in the first leg. Today we just went for it, and we came up with a performance %1s fans could be proud of. That's how I want us to approach every game from now on.
Let's take one step at a time.

I hope the lads' self-belief will take a big boost from what we've achieved here. But we're not where we want to be yet, in finals and semi-finals. Let's keep our feet on the ground and take things one game at a time.
We showed so much desire.

A great team performance. We had leaders all over the pitch today. The boys grabbed the game by the scruff and didn't let go. There's a special spirit in the %1s dressing room. And it's what makes comebacks like this one possible.
